# ==============================================================================
# FILE: .env.example
# PURPOSE: Template for the environment variables file.
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file:  cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your actual values in the new .env file.
#   3. NEVER commit .env to version control (it is in .gitignore).
#
# ACADEMIC NOTE — 12-Factor App / Secrets Management:
#   Hardcoding secrets (API keys, passwords) directly in source code is one
#   of the most common and serious security mistakes in software development.
#   The 12-Factor App methodology (https://12factor.net/) mandates storing
#   config in environment variables so that:
#     1. Secrets are never in version control history.
#     2. The same codebase can run in dev/staging/production with different keys.
#     3. A leaked repo does NOT mean leaked credentials.
# ==============================================================================

# --- Google Gemini API Key ---
# Obtain from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# Format: A long alphanumeric string starting with "AI..."
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
